KW  - Forecasting the forecasts of others
KW  - Higher order beliefs
KW  - Pooling equilibrium
KW  - Recursive methods
KW  - Kalman filter
AB  - We apply recursive methods to obtain a finite dimensional and recursive representation of an equilibrium of one of Townsend's models of ‘forecasting the forecasts of others’. The equilibrium has the property that decision makers make common forecasts of the hidden state variable whose presence motivates them to pay attention to prices in other markets. Thus, the model has too few sources of randomness to put decision makers into a situation where they should form ‘higher order beliefs’ (i.e., beliefs about others' beliefs). In Townsend's model, they know the beliefs of others because they share them. We attain our finite-dimensional recursive representation by applying methods of Pearlman, Currie, and Levine [Economic Modelling 3(2) (1986) 90].
